No fewer than nine persons, including the
driver of a commercial bus, were feared dead when the vehicle plunged into a riv- er in Kware local government area of Soko- to State. The incident, according to eyewitness ac-
count, happened around 12noon on Thurs- day along the Kware-Geadanlbawa-Illela Road. Neither the vehicle nor its occupants were recovered at the time of filing this re- port.
The eyewitness who gave his name as She- hu Wurno, said about eight
passengers were in the ill-fated vehicle
with the driver as the ninth person.
When contacted the State Emergency Management Agency (SEMA), director of Relief and Rehabilitation, Mustapha Umar, said they were still searching for the dead bodies and vehicle. Mustapha, however, said he could not
confirm the number of passengers in the
vehicle, adding they had sent crane to the place while local divers are making frantic effort to recover the bodies and vehicle.
On his part, the spokesman of the Na- tional Emergency Management Agency (NEMA), Aliyu Muhammad, confirmed the incident, adding their men were on the site on a search and rescue mission